Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the estimation of signal to noise ratio (SNR) which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the tracking of SNR for handover and radio link failure detection, which are important aspects of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of millimeter wave frequencies in 5G cellular systems, which are likely to be used for multimedia applications. 
4. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the dynamics of the channel and SNR tracking, which are important aspects of communication and networking. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method using real experiments, which involves the use of systems and control techniques.
